1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,916
Amazon Translate Overview

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,124
Amazon Translate is a text translation
service

3
00:00:08,166 --> 00:00:10,958
that uses advanced machine learning
technologies

4
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:13,000
to provide translation on demand.

5
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:18,208
Amazon Translate uses attention mechanisms
to understand context.

6
00:00:19,250 --> 00:00:22,125
These mechanisms help Amazon Translate
decide

7
00:00:22,166 --> 00:00:23,916
which words in the source text

8
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:25,250
are most relevant

9
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:27,250
for generating the next target word.

10
00:00:28,291 --> 00:00:30,541
Amazon Translate can automatically

11
00:00:30,541 --> 00:00:32,249
detect the language used

12
00:00:32,249 --> 00:00:33,541
in your source text.

13
00:00:34,458 --> 00:00:38,541
You can use Amazon Translate to translate
unstructured text documents,

14
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:41,791
or to build applications that work in
multiple languages.

15
00:00:43,791 --> 00:00:45,791
Amazon Translate Use Cases

16
00:00:46,875 --> 00:00:49,000
Translate user-generated content

17
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:51,416
Automatically translate

18
00:00:51,541 --> 00:00:54,600
high volumes of user-generated content in real time,

19
00:00:55,125 --> 00:00:57,458
such as social media feed stories,

20
00:00:57,541 --> 00:00:59,141
profile descriptions,

21
00:00:59,208 --> 00:01:00,208
and comments.

22
00:01:01,625 --> 00:01:04,624
Analyze online conversations in different
languages.

23
00:01:04,999 --> 00:01:09,000
Understand sentiments toward your brand,
product, or service

24
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:12,250
by using a natural language processing
application

25
00:01:12,416 --> 00:01:15,125
that analyzes text in multiple languages.

26
00:01:16,291 --> 00:01:19,375
Create cross-lingual communications
between users.

27
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:24,166
Add real-time translation within chat,
email, helpdesk,

28
00:01:24,208 --> 00:01:26,000
and ticketing applications,

29
00:01:26,291 --> 00:01:28,208
so that an English-speaking agent

30
00:01:28,291 --> 00:01:30,166
can communicate with customers

31
00:01:30,291 --> 00:01:32,208
across multiple languages.

32
00:01:33,375 --> 00:01:36,333
Amazon Translate Benefits

33
00:01:37,208 --> 00:01:38,958
Uses deep learning techniques.

34
00:01:40,208 --> 00:01:43,083
Amazon Translate uses deep learning
techniques

35
00:01:43,708 --> 00:01:45,708
that consider the entire context

36
00:01:46,125 --> 00:01:47,583
of the source sentence

37
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:50,416
and the translation it has generated so
far

38
00:01:50,666 --> 00:01:51,596
to produce more accurate and fluent
translation.

39
00:01:51,791 --> 00:01:55,375
Perform batch and real-time translations.

40
00:01:55,408 --> 00:01:58,291
Amazon Translate can perform batch
translations

41
00:01:58,775 --> 00:02:01,117
when you have large quantities

42
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:02,366
of text to translate.

43
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:05,300
It can perform real-time translations

44
00:02:05,366 --> 00:02:07,299
when you want to deliver

45
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:10,289
on-demand translations of content

46
00:02:10,291 --> 00:02:12,291
as a feature of your applications.

47
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:17,250
Customize translations

48
00:02:17,258 --> 00:02:18,041
You can use the following settings

49
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:20,083
to customize the translations

50
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:21,938
that you produce with Amazon Translate.

51
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:24,200
The Do Not Translate Tag setting.

52
00:02:24,216 --> 00:02:24,500
specifies content

53
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:28,125
that you do not want to translate.

54
00:02:28,366 --> 00:02:31,316
The custom terminology setting helps to
define

55
00:02:31,700 --> 00:02:37,291
how you want Amazon Translate to translate specific terms such as brand names. 

56
00:02:37,575 --> 00:02:43,350
The profanity setting masks profane words and phrases in your translation output.

57
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:49,600
Set the level of language formality in your translation output.

58
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:56,708
The Parallel Data setting helps you customize the output of your batch translations
jobs.

59
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:57,100
.

60
00:02:57,583 --> 00:03:02,750
This is the end of Amazon Translate
overview. Thanks for watching.

